      "content": "This \"exit opportunity\" argument is a classic economic defense used by tech giants to justify their predatory acquisition strategies. While it is true that the promise of a sale can motivate founders, it is a cynical tactic that allows monopolies to buy up promising innovations before they can truly disrupt the market, effectively killing competition rather than fostering it. The reality is that these deals often serve to lock in existing advantages rather than reward genuine, independent innovation.",
